Key Match Events: Nick Castellanos hit a two-run homer in the first inning and scored the winning run in the sixth.
Zack Wheeler pitched six innings, allowing two runs on four hits and three walks with nine strikeouts.
José Alvarado pitched five scoreless innings, allowing only one hit and one walk while striking out seven.
Weston Wilson's swinging bunt single in the sixth inning scored Castellanos from third to give the Phillies the lead.
Aramis Garcia tagged out a runner at the plate in the fourth and threw out a runner at second who represented the potential tying run in the ninth.
Pre-Game Insights: The Phillies played without Alec Bohm and J.T. Realmuto for the entire series.
They played more than half the series without Kyle Schwarber, who tweaked his left elbow on Tuesday.
The team got solid starting pitching and a nearly flawless performance from the bullpen, along with key contributions from unlikely sources.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Rob Thomson emphasized the importance of continued effort until the division is clinched.
Zack Wheeler feels comfortable and hopes to continue his strong performance.
José Alvarado expressed confidence in his recent resurgence and commitment to competing.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillies have an eight-game lead over the Mets in the NL East with 16 games to play.
They could clinch their first division title sometime next week, especially if they play well against the Mets this weekend.
